# Editing Guidelines

## Respect Existing Patterns

Before introducing a new pattern or abstraction, check how similar problems are already solved in the codebase and follow the same approach. Only introduce a new pattern if there is a clear reason the existing one cannot work.

## Verify Fixes

Never assume a change will successfully fix something. Every fix must be verified:

- Run the relevant code path or test after applying the fix
- Do not mark a task complete until verification passes

## Keep Console Logs During a Fix

Do not remove `console.log` statements while actively making a change. Keep them until the fix is confirmed working. Remove logging only after verification.

## Keep Documentation Accurate

When changing code that is described in `docs/`, update the documentation in the same step. Do not leave docs out of sync with the implementation.
